30/12/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Officials say a specialised anti-drug police unit uncovered a drug production laboratory Wednesday (29 December) and found 120kg of substances used to produce amphetamines.
The value of the seized substances was estimated at over 220m euros.
Police say the material was stored in the basement of a house occupied by a man with a criminal record.
The basement was allegedly equipped for drug production.
Police are searching for two suspected accomplices.
(BTA, BNT, Mediapool - 29/12/04)
